    <note type="dates"><date>1806–77</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Merchant. East India Merchant in Singapore and Australia until 1846, when he returned to London and founded the house of Ashton &amp; Co. (later Gilman Bros. &amp; Co.), London agents for his brother’s firm, Messrs Gilman &amp; Co., in China. Patron of the living of Chudleigh, Devon.</p></note>
